content.rendered:
Excited to share my live set as direct support for Madeaux in San Francisco for the LIMBO world tour. This was an incredible SOLD OUT show at Halcyon SF, and it was even better when Confession label OG Jace Mek showed up as our surprise guest when Madeaux, Jace Mek, and myself all went b3b till 4AM to close out the night for “what may have been one of the best sets of all time” as Jace Mek wrote in his Instagram post this week.

BAKR is a DJ & Producer from the Bay Area known for his unique approach to mixing house music. BAKR’s music will get you moving with his punchy baselines and melodic rhythms, oftentimes mixed with hip-hop, R&B, pop and more. He seeks inspiration from nearly all genres of electronic music, but his core identity stems from the sounds of tech-house, bass-house, and G-house music.

As the founder & CEO of GCODE, an electronic music events company, BAKR put himself on the map by organizing, promoting, and hosting unique, large-scale events. As a resident of some of the city’s most iconic venues. he’s regularly supporting some of the biggest artists in the game. You can find BAKR spinning any given weekend amongst San Francisco’s hottest nightclubs including 1015 Folsom, Audio SF, Halcyon SF, and Public Works, supporting some of the world’s biggest acts including Anna Lunoe, Boombox Cartel, Cazzette, Moon Boots, Zeds Dead, Dom Dolla, Le Youth, Madeaux, Dr. Fresch, Bijou, Sonny Fodera, Dom Dolla and many more!

title.rendered: DJ Nick Stracener – Love and Lust In Music We Trust

content.rendered:
This month is the either the loved or hated holiday of Valentines <3….I wanted to create a mix that would take you on a love or hate relationship. One thing is for sure you guys; whether you are single or in a relationship there is one thing you can always count on and this is MUSIC. So I titled this track “Love & Lust In Music We Trust”! Enjoy!

Nick Stracener is a self taught DJ. He started as a gogo dancer then worked his way to promoting events and then he decided to purse the art of dj’ing! He is a trained saxophonist and has played the sax for 17 years. His style of music is house, tribal house, and he likes a lot of upbeat vocals and remixing current songs!

Listen to the mix! DJ Nick Stracener-Love and Lust In Music We Trust

Start in 2015, AMON is the second project oriented (House, G-House, Nudisco, BassHouse, DeepHouse) of the Belgian dj/producer called (????) with this new project more groovy it’s like a return to the source with many vocals and a speed not exceed 123bpm and highlighting the music before image. He isn’t a newbie, his career is proof. Indeed, with his old electro project he has already played in several countries in the world to make people dance with his electro sounds ( Russia, Germany, Canada, Slovenia, Portugal, France, Netherlands, Colombia, Belgium, etc….) And in Belgium he has played in the best clubs/party like (Culture Club, Café d’Anvers, Vooruit, Silo, Cadran, Body to Body, Legendz, Beats of Love, Kozzmozz, EazyF*ck, Dissonant festival, Nandrin festival, City Parade,…and many many more.

Played also with big name like Digitalism, Steve Aoki, Designers Drugs, Mustard Pimp, You Killing Me, Teenage Bad Girl, Modek, The subs, Alex Gopher, Das Glow, Fukkk off, The Glimmers, Rex The Dog, GTronic, Sebastian, Dr Lektroluv, The Hacker, David Carretta, Miss Kittin, Anthony Rother, etc….
